Lat72.label: APOE-Centric Alzheimer's Disease Mechanism
Lat72.primary_mechanism: APOE ε4-mediated amyloid-β deposition, impaired lipid transport, and neuronal vulnerability
Lat72.biological_interpretation: This factor isolates the well-established APOE locus effect on late-onset Alzheimer's disease. The 19q13.32 region encompasses APOE, TOMM40, and APOC1, with APOE ε4 being the strongest common genetic risk factor for Alzheimer's disease (Corder et al., Science 1993). The co-loading of cholesterol-related traits reflects APOE's dual role in peripheral lipid metabolism and central nervous system cholesterol homeostasis.
